# Delegate to user (save tokens)

When planning or finishing a task, **split work explicitly**:

## User does (prefer delegating — do not run long command batches unless asked)

- Apply Supabase migrations in SQL Editor (`app/supabase/README.txt` steps)
- Run `npm run` / `e2e:*` / `deploy:check` locally and paste failures only
- Manual UI QA (Settings, print bill, Excel CSV open, stock adjustment smoke)
- Product/branding decisions (lock name in `app/src/config/productBrand.ts`)
- Git commit, push, Netlify deploy, Supabase dashboard config
- Accountant / CA review of sample exports

## Agent does

- Multi-file features, `domainLive`, hooks, migrations **files**, export lib, Settings refactors
- Fixing build/type errors from user-pasted logs
- Docs updates per `docs-on-change.mdc` when shipping behavior

## Response format

End implementation summaries with a **Your turn** section: numbered steps, exact commands, expected pass criteria. Keep agent runs to code + short `e2e:export`-style source checks only when user did not ask to run full matrix/live.
